The camera access was a default permission included in the initial setup—I have removed it in the code update below to ensure your dashboard only requests what it actually needs.

Regarding the **Backend**: A web dashboard (Frontend) cannot run a Node.js server or an MQTT broker directly inside the browser for security reasons. Your backend is the "Bridge" that must run on your laptop or a server.

Here is the code for the other two parts of your system to be kept outside the dashboard:

### 1. The Bridge (Backend - Node.js)
Run this on your laptop to connect the hardware to the dashboard.
**Command:** `npm install mqtt ws sqlite3`

```javascript
const mqtt = require('mqtt');
const WebSocket = require('ws');
const sqlite3 = require('sqlite3').verbose();

// Pillar 1: Local Storage
const db = new sqlite3.Database('./iot_logs.db');
db.run("CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS readings (room TEXT, temp REAL, humidity REAL, time DATETIME)");

// Pillar 2: The Gateway (WebSocket for Dashboard)
const wss = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 8080 });

// Pillar 3: MQTT Connection
const mqttClient = mqtt.connect('mqtts://your-hivemq-id.hivemq.cloud', {
  username: 'your_user', password: 'your_password'
});

mqttClient.on('connect', () => mqttClient.subscribe('home/sensors'));

mqttClient.on('message', (topic, message) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(message.toString());

  // 1. Save to SQLite
  db.run("INSERT INTO readings VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)", 
    [data.room, data.temp, data.humidity, new Date().toISOString()]);

  // 2. Broadcast to Dashboard
  wss.clients.forEach(client => {
    if (client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) client.send(JSON.stringify(data));
  });
});
```

### 2. The Edge (Firmware - ESP32)
Flash this to your ESP32 using the Arduino IDE.

```cpp
#include <WiFi.h>
#include <PubSubClient.h>
#include <ArduinoJson.h>

const char* ssid = "WIFI_NAME";
const char* password = "WIFI_PASSWORD";
const char* mqtt_server = "your-hivemq-id.hivemq.cloud";

WiFiClientSecure espClient;
PubSubClient client(espClient);

void loop() {
  StaticJsonDocument<200> doc;
  doc["room"] = "Living Room";
  doc["temp"] = 24.5; // Read from DHT22 sensor here
  doc["humidity"] = 50;

  char buffer[256];
  serializeJson(doc, buffer);
  client.publish("home/sensors", buffer);
  delay(5000);
}
```

### 3. Dashboard Code Updates
I have removed the camera permissions and deleted the `ArchitectureGuide.tsx` file from your project as requested.

